title: Adeline
lyrics:
Oh, my Adeline, ooooh
Down in Tasmania
Where the devil's jaws are far too weak
To tear you away
Ooh, I wish you well

I wish you well

I wish you well

I wish you well



Oh, my Adeline

I watch your morning swim again

Oh, cold from the blue sky

Strokes from passing mopeds

My sweet Adeline



Ooh, I wish you well (my Adeline)

I wish you well

I wish you well (my Adeline)

I wish you well



And the old triangle went jingle jangle

On the Royal Canal

My Adeline was swimming

Sweet Adeline was singing

To the tune of Royal Canal



Swim

Swim on

Swim on

Swim on

Swim

Swim on

Swim on

Swim on



And the old triangle went jingle jangle

On the Royal Canal

My Adeline was swimming

Sweet Adeline was singing

To the tune of Royal Canal



I wish her well

I wish her well

I wish her well

I wish her well

I wish her well
